"title": "2033: Jesus Christ, humanity of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2033",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture stresses the total humanity of Jesus Christ. Although sinless, Christ shared in the general condition of humanity, including suffering and death.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ was a man</h2>\n<h3>By his own claims</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:40\">JHN 8:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:20\">MAT 8:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:58\">LUK 9:58</a></p>\n<h3>In statements made by others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:5\">JHN 19:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:27\">MAT 8:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:39\">MRK 15:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:47\">LUK 23:47</a> <em>the centurion</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:2\">LUK 15:2</a> <em>the Pharisees and teachers of the law</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:18\">LUK 23:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:33\">JHN 1:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:42\">JHN 4:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:12\">JHN 7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:15\">JHN 7:15</a> <em>some Jews</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:27\">JHN 7:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:33\">JHN 9:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:47\">JHN 11:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:22-Acts2:23\">ACT 2:22–2:23</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ shared in the general condition of humanity</h2>\n<h3>He assumed human nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a></strong> <em>“flesh” here speaks not only of a material body but also of human nature.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:7-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:7–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:2\">1JN 4:2</a></p>\n<h3>He had a human descent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:3\">ROM 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:1\">MAT 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:54-Matt13:56\">MAT 13:54–13:56</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:2-Mark6:3\">MRK 6:2–6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:5\">ROM 9:5</a></p>\n<h3>He had a normal body which could be handled and touched</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1\">1JN 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:36\">MAT 14:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:56\">MRK 6:56</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:28\">LUK 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>He had a soul</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:38\">MAT 26:38</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:34\">MRK 14:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:11\">ISA 53:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ partook of human experience</h2>\n<h3>He was born</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4\">GAL 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:6-Luke2:7\">LUK 2:6–2:7</a></p>\n<h3>He grew and developed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:40\">LUK 2:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:52\">LUK 2:52</a></p>\n<h3>He was hungry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:18\">MAT 21:18</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:12\">MRK 11:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:2\">MAT 4:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:2\">LUK 4:2</a></p>\n<h3>He was thirsty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:28\">JHN 19:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:7\">JHN 4:7</a></p>\n<h3>He was tired</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:6\">JHN 4:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He slept</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:24\">MAT 8:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:38\">MRK 4:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:23\">LUK 8:23</a></p>\n<h3>He was tempted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:18\">HEB 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1\">MAT 4:1</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:13\">MRK 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:2\">LUK 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></p>\n<h3>He suffered</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:1\">1PE 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:22\">COL 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7-Heb5:8\">HEB 5:7–5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10\">HEB 10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a></p>\n<h3>He died</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:50\">MAT 27:50</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:37\">MRK 15:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:46\">LUK 23:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:30\">JHN 19:30</a> <em>Jesus Christ most closely identified with the rest of humanity through his death. However Jesus Christ is distinct from human beings in that his death was an act of free will and not the inevitable consequence of sin (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:17-John10:18\">Jn 10:17–18</a>).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:9\">HEB 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>The risen Christ has human characteristics</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:37-Luke24:43\">LUK 24:37–24:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:27\">JHN 20:27</a></p>\n<h2>The returning Christ retains his human identity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:11\">ACT 1:11</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ was a sinless human being</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></strong> <em>Sinlessness does not make Jesus Christ less human. It is sin that degrades humanity.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:41\">LUK 23:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:47\">LUK 23:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a></p>\n<h2>The necessity of Jesus Christ's humanity</h2>\n<h3>As a man Jesus Christ made atonement for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:18-Rom5:19\">ROM 5:18–5:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12-Rom5:17\">ROM 5:12–5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5\">1TI 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17\">HEB 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>As a man Jesus Christ gives the gift of resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:21\">1CO 15:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:45\">1CO 15:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20-Phil3:21\">PHP 3:20–3:21</a></p>\n<h3>As a man Jesus Christ is able to help others in their need</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:18\">HEB 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15-Heb5:2\">HEB 4:15–5:2</a></p>\n<h3>As a man Jesus Christ is the perfect example</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:5–2:8</a></p>",
